Rob Griffin

Currently working as a programmer at AstraZeneca in Sweden, I use SAS and R for statistical programming. I began programming during my PhD in evolutionary biology, where I used R for analysis, data visualisation and other data science tasks. My interest in programming grew through my two postdoctoral positions in Finland and Australia, where I learnt and experimented with some basics of languages including Python, Java, Kotlin, HTML, CSS and JavaScript in my spare time.

In 2020, I decided that I wanted to pursue this interest and place programming at core of my career. I joined a graduate program in biometrics at AstraZeneca, being promoted from the two-year program after the first year. Over the last two years, I have continued to advance my programming skills, learning SAS through AstraZeneca, working to advance the adoption of R at AstraZeneca, and using free time to take courses in Java and Kotlin and self-teach other languages. As an example, I built this page using an experimental mix of R, RMarkdown, HTML, JavaScript and CSS as a learning exercise.

Going forward, I am looking for a role where programming is not just a tool to be used, but where problem solving with high quality, efficient and creative code is of real value to the business. I am most interested in positions within the vicinity of Gothenburg or Vnersborg/Trollhttan, offering the opportunity to build upon the foundational skills I have, opportunities for development long-term within the company, and the chance to use programming within a variety of contexts.

Education

  • PhD in Biology, specialising in Evolutionary Genetics. Uppsala University, 2015.
  • MSc in Evolutionary and Behavioural Ecology. University of Exeter, 2011.
  • BSc in Conservation Biology and Ecology. University of Exeter, 2010.

  • Postdoctoral Researcher, University of Turku (FIN). Mar 2016 to Aug 2018.
  • PhD Candidate, Uppsala University. Sep 2011 to Sep 2015.
  • Assistant Manager, Falmouth Townhouse Hotel and Bar (GBR). Feb 2011 to Aug 2011.
  • Supervisor, Harbour View Restaurant (GBR). Jul 2008 to Sep 2010.
